    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not about not being perfect, though. it's deeper than that. it feels like it's just a lost cause. like, if you try to fix a piece of glass that's been shattered into a thousand tiny bits... you can glue it back together, sure, but it's still broken. it's still sharp and jagged and full of cracks. you can't ever make it whole again. i feel like i'm just living in the cracks. do you think it's possible for something to just be too broken to ever be whole again?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
